Name: Wayfinder Kollaps 16oz
Description: The city of Cologne on the Rhine river in western Germany is renowned for its “Kölsch” beer. Although it utilizes a top-fermenting ale yeast, Kölsch is fermented relatively cold and further cold-conditioned. The purity law of 1516 outlaws using any wheat in lager beer, but since it’s an ale, Kölsch uses up to 20%. It ends up being very clear and yellow, with a slightly fruity aroma, and a sharp crispness.

Name: La Chouffe 11.2oz
Description: The gnomes of Fairyland are particularly fond of this golden beer. LA CHOUFFE, with its slight hoppy taste, combining notes of fresh coriander and fruity tones, is the drink which gives them their zest for life. At least, that's what these imps say when they are thirsty. Their secret used to be jealously guarded from one generation to the next until the day they shared the recipe with humans to seal their friendship. Of all the legends from the wonderful region of the Belgian Ardennes, the tale of LA CHOUFFE is the one which most merits re-telling.

Name: HUB When Life Gives You Blueberries 16oz
Kostritzer Schwarzbier 500ml
Description: Since April 1991, the Köstritzer black beer brewery, a subsidiary of the Bitburger brewery, has emerged as of one of the most modern breweries in Thuringia. In September 1993, it was with great pride we (re-) introduced the "original Köstritzer black beer".

Name: Urban Roots Virtual Connection
Description: A Belgian Pale Ale collaboration with Allagash Brewing. This beer features Saphir and Tettnang hops fermented with Belgian yeast. It’s fruity, hoppy, slightly bitter and refreshingly crisp. <U+2800><U+2800>

Name: Mason Ale Works Big Time Cosmic Revelation
Description: Hazy Double IPA Double Dry Hopped with Galaxy and Citra

Name: Mason Ale Works Party in the Back
Description: Double Dry Hopped w/Pineapple

Description: West Coast Unfiltered IPA

Name: Mason Ale Ball Don’t Lie
Description: A classic West Coast Style IPA in celebration of the NBA's return!

Name: Mason Ale Works Three Fisted Humdinger
Description: Hazy Double IPA Double Dry Hopped with Citra

Name: Bear Republic Racer 5 16oz
Description: This hoppy IPA is a full bodied beer brewed with malted barley, wheat, and crystal malts. The malt base is designed to highlight the unique floral qualities of Columbus and Cascade hops from the Pacific Northwest. There’s a trophy in every glass!

Name: Ex Novo Unstuck In Time/Reverse Whirlpool/Cozy Chaos 16oz
Description: Tangerine, ripe melon, peach

Name: Coldfire Nelson IPA
Description: The Nelson hop is a beautiful example of the unique expression terroir contributes to flavor. This intriguing New Zealand variety is often described as having flavors and aromas of sauvignon blanc, fresh goose berries, citrus, lychee and spice. In this version of the Discoverer series, we blended Nelson, Mosaic and Citra Hops to create layers of fruit flavor intrigue in this refreshing, golden hued IPA.

Name: Coldfire Galaxy DIPA
Description: This DIPA produces big well balanced flavors that include; mango, pineapple, grapefruit. It's tropical, juicy, and dank.

Name: Ferment Black is Beautiful
Description: Black is Beautiful is a collaborative effort to raise awareness for the injustices people of color face daily and raise funds for police brutality reform and legal defenses for those who have been wronged. Fremont Brewing will donate the proceeds to the NAACP Legal Defense Fund.

Name: Ferment Dry Stout
Description: Ferment Dry Stout embodies the spirit of the extremely quaffable, midnight-black ales of Dublin. A pale mash and unique black sparge technique imparts a gentle acidity to the beer along with a clean, delicate roast character in this surprisingly refreshing dark ale.

Name: Heater Allen Bobtoberfest / Marzen
Description: Bobtoberfest is our version of an Oktoberfest-style beer and our most popular seasonal. This beer is named for owner, Rick Allen's, late brother Bob, the person who sparked his interest in brewing lager beers in general and Oktoberfest beers in particular. Bright amber in color; rich, malty, and smooth, with a just touch of clean hop bitterness. If you can't make it to Munich this fall, this beer is the next best thing.

Name: Unibroue Blanche De Chambly 16oz
Description: (White of Chambly) was the first bottle

Name: Rogue Black Is Beautiful 16oz
Description: Black Lager with a mellow combination of roast coffee, caramel and chocolate. There will be a hint of tropical fruitiness from the hops to compliment the chocolate notes. A good balance of lager drinkability and big flavors from the roast malts. 5% ABV

Name: Knee Deep Breaking Bud 16oz
Description: Old school meets new school in this fresh approach to the classic IPA. At 50 IBU’s and 6.7% ABV, Breaking Bud features the restrained bitterness and alcohol of a classic IPA with newer tropical fruit hop flavors and aromas of Mosaic. Also in the hop mix are Simcoe and CTZ, creating layers of mango, passion fruit, pine and dank. A malt bill with a pinch of crystal malt and a hefty dose of flaked wheat keeps the beer crisp while adding flavor complexity. Cheers to the past, present and future!

Name: Crux Velvet Underpants 16oz
Description: Add this silky, smooth Hazy to your IPA playlist and prepare to rock out to tropical notes of mango, pine, and stone fruit balanced by a soft and fluffy mouthfeel. Loaded exclusively with Mosaic hops, this is a Hazy IPA you’ll want to put on repeat.

Name: Culmination Neon Valley 16oz
Description: Pineapple, Guava, Cherry. On nitro.

Name: Paulaner Grapefruit Radler 500ml
Description: Natur pur: Fruchtige Grapefruitnoten treffen auf feinen Hellbiergeschmack.

Name: Paulaner Original Munich Lager 500ml
Beer: Paulaner Original Münchner Hell / Premium Lager / Munich Lager
Description: Our Original Munich Lager is a true classic with its clear and bright gold sparkling hue, crowned by a pure white head. A beer which always goes down well: mild, elegant malts, with a hint of sweetness and a soft hint of hops in the background. This Munich beer is ideal to accompany spare ribs and spicy dishes. Just try it!

Name: Fullers ESB 500ml
Description: ESB was launched into the Fuller's family in 1971, as a winter brew to replace a beer named Old Burton Extra.

Name: Oregonic Tonic White Peach
Description: It smells like freshly sliced peaches and tastes like lounging in the shade on a sunny afternoon. It is summer in a bottle (in the winter we drink it to remind ourselves that the sun exists).

Name: Humble Sea Socks & Sandals
Description: Foggy IPA with Citra, Centennial, Simcoe, and Chinook.

Name: Beachwood Simcoast To Coast IPA 16oz
Description: Side to side, back to front, coast to coast, 100% Simcoe!

Name: Humble Sea The Stoke is No Joke
Description: Double whirlpooled, double dry hopped west coast DIPA fused with simcoe and strata hops.

Name: Hen House Oyster Stout
Description: We brew this beer in tribute to the waterways and ecosystems that have made this region of California so vital for so long. Whole Oysters from Hog Island Oyster Company and a touch of sea salt imbue flavors of the sea. The calcium from the oysters brings out the chocolate and coffee notes from California-grown malt from Admiral Maltings in Alameda. HenHouse Oyster Stout is a beer with true terroir of both Bodega Bay and California's Central Valley.

Name: Urban Family Crucial Velocity/You Are Not Alone 16oz
Bend Brewing Ching Ching 16oz
Description: It is effervescent with a SweeTART tanginess. Brewed with pomegranate and hibiscus this yum-yum is a perfect thirst quencher that just might push the boundaries of what you consider beer.

Name: Rev Nat’s Punch 16oz
Description: This super Summer refresher of fresh blood orange juice, ripe watermelon, Indian mangoes & a punch of spicy ginger is not overly sweet.

Name: Aslan Cosmic Dreams 12oz
Description: Cosmic Dreams is a Hazy IPA with notes of freshly pressed tangerine, mandarin, and navel orange juice Following in the footsteps of Batch 15, this IPA is dry, with a quenching bitterness and a pointed goodness character feat. Pacific Gem, Amarillo, El Dorado, & Simcoe Designed with a slightly lower alcohol content for longevity and reduced calories, Aslan is happy to add this new offering to their flagship family!

Name: Athletic Run Wild 12oz
Description: The ultimate session-able IPA. Brewed with a blend of Northwest hops with Citra and Mosaic at the forefront. Body of premium organic malts from US & Germany. Subtle yet complex malt profile.

Name: Athletic Upside Dawn 12oz
Description: Refreshing, clean, balanced, light-bodied. Aromas subtle with floral and earthy notes. Brewed with premium organic malts from US & Germany along with combo of English and traditional American hops to the golden ale style. 50 Calories.

Name: CCU Cascadia 16oz
Description: This is a true dry cider, made with the finest American dessert apples and crafted with French saison yeast. Cloudy and golden colored, it is best served chilled, not ice cold.

Name: Konrad 14
Description: Konrad 14º is a classic Czech lager, but with more weight and more bitter hops than the typical Bohemian session beer. Golden, full-bodied, and loaded with fresh, clean Czech malt, the 14º finishes with a burst of noble Žatec (Saaz) hops.

Name: Stiegl Radler 500ml
Description: Real grapefruit juice gives this deliciously refreshing Radler (mixed beer drink) its amber natural cloudiness and pleasant tangy taste. The refreshingly fruity taste makes Stiegl-Radler Grapefruit a wonderful thirst quencher.

Name: Stiegl Radler Zitrone 16oz
Description: NB: Sold with 2% and 2.5% ABV - please do not post an edit request asking to change it from one to the other.

Name: Alpenfire Glow Aerlie Red 750ml
Description: This single varietal Heritage Rosé cider made from organic red fleshed apples named Airlie Redflesh. It retains the beautiful color, aroma and candy apple flavor of the fruit with a slow cool fermentation then matured for 9+months in stainless before bottling. No coloring or other adjuncts are added to make and retain this color.

Name: Rev Nat’s Viva La Pineapple 12oz
Description: This summer seasonal is a blend of ¡Tepache! and cider. Mucho delicious!

Name: Chimay Grande Reserve 11.2oz
Beer: Chimay Grande Réserve Vieillie en Barriques - Chêne francais, Chêne américain, Rhum - 29/08/2017

Name: 3F Cuvee Armand & Gaston 1.5L
Beer: 3 Fonteinen Oude Geuze Cuvée Armand & Gaston
Description: 3 Fonteinen Oude Geuze Cuvée Armand & Gaston is a blend of one-, two-, and three-year old traditional lambics, all brewed at Brouwerij 3 Fonteinen. Spontaneous fermentation, patient maturation in oak barrels, and continued evolution in the bottle result in a distinctively complex beer. No two bottlings are alike, as there are multiple variables in the blending process, a variety of barrel sizes and shapes, differences in aged lambic proportions, etc. This cuvée, like all of our lambic, is 100% natural, authentic, spontaneously fermented, and crafted with steadfast adherence to tradition, like Armand and Gaston Debelder have always done it. This geuze has fermented in the bottle and will continue to develop its tastes and aromas over its long life when properly cellared. Traditional Lambic is living, cultural heritage rooted in the Zenne valley! Taste, savour, enjoy, and experience this unfiltered, unpasteurised, and unadulterated beer with friends new and old!

Name: Suzies Hard Seltzer
Description: Experimental Hard Seltzer

Name: Foam Brewers Pop Crimes
Description: Double dry-hopped with copious amounts of select Enigma and Citra hops, this 10 percent beer is a monster through and through. Tropical hop aromas are bursting out, complimented with some mild berry notes and a soft but resinous finish.

Name: Foam Brewers Local Dork
Description: tasting notes: honeydew, citrus, vanilla

Name: Adroit Theory Dead & Gone DIPA 16oz
Description: A modern + hazy take on an IPA. highly aromatic, pillowy and soft malt, with a low-bitterness, and semi-sweet finish.

Name: Ex Novo Marryin Berries/Cactus Wins The Lottery/Puff Puff Passion 12oz
Description: Made for the assistant brewer's wedding this kettle sour is made with white wheat, flaked oats, marrionberries, raspberries, and mosaic.

Name: Urban Roots Kind For Nothing 16oz
Description: Kind For Nothing is a special collaboration IPA with our friends @Kindhumans filled with a special blend of kindness plus Citra and Strata hops then fermented with a fruity and expressive yeast. Kindhumans celebrates the good in humanity by cultivating a community of kindness, promoting conscious consumption, and always giving back.

Name: Moonraker Some Grass IPA
Description: Strata and citra. Billows of dank fruity pebble oil cloudz. Smells like 2 and 1/2 small oranges that look like tangerines.

Name: Moonraker Cool Cool 16oz
Description: Hop forward, tropical NE IPA with a fresh, piney, mild hop bite. Notes of mango, guava, pineapple, fruit punch. Medium body, mild bitterness. Mosaic & Galaxy

Name: Moonraker/Alvarado Street West Coast 16oz
Description: YOJO, our New England style IPA. This beer uses a proprietary English yeast strain and is completely unfined and unfiltered. Tons of apricot, peach, and pineapple hop flavors from the use of Galaxy, Mosaic, Simcoe, Citra, and CTZ. 6.5% ABV, 50 IBU.

Name: Trap Door Clouded Memories
Description: Hazy Pale Ale with Citra, Bru-1 and Nelson Sauvin. Light bodied, pineapple, strawberry bubblegum, lemon zest.

Name: HenHouse Sweet life
Description: We took our Best Life Blond Ale and threw in some mango, peach & lime pure´e to give y’all mad fruit vibes. Like, just a hint of fruit up in here just to brighten up this already bodacious blond. For those days where the sun keeps yah warm, this beer is here to keep y’all v cool. Or crisp? Maybe both. DEFINITELY the fuegoest blond on the block. Get like us!

Name: Equilibrium Fractal
Description: Fractal Citra/Mosaic investigates the interplay between Citra, Mosaic, and our slightly revised processes. Fractal Citra & Mosaic pours a resinous-hazy-straw yellow releasing complex aromas of dank citrus, passion fruit, earthy grass, and tropical melon. The taste is resinous, dank pineapple juice, touch of pine, and ends with a slightly creamy mouthfeel and a firm but rounded bitterness.

Name: Equilibrium Flux Fluid
Description: Knowing this beer would come out around the long weekend; Pete, Ryan, and Jessie discussed flavors that were both refreshing and tropical for Flux Fluid and used hops with notes you may find in your favorite cocktail. It starts of with oats and wheat and a whirlpool of Simcoe before being heavily dry hopped with BRU-1, Sabro, and Motueka. Hazy yellow, in color this beer has flavors of orange peel, papaya, lime, pineapple, and berries with a hint of coconut. A creamy mouthfeel leads the way to its juicy and smoooooth finish. The ABV is undetectable for a beer this size so enjoy with care, this fluid will sneak up on you.

Name: Second Profession Space Flamingo
Description: Nice aromatic example of a N. E. Style IPA. Notes of passion fruit, pappaya, orange and lemon.

Name: Revision Disco Ninja
Description: It’s a simple universal fact that ninjas are badass. You know what else is badass? Revision beer. Our buddies at Shoe Tree Brewing kicked around ideas with us to develop this tasty, tantalizing, karate chop in your freaking mouth. Kaleidoscopic nunchuck hits to the dome with Citra, Galaxy, Mosaic and Amarillo. Stealthily slaying your taste buds, one sip at a time.

Name: Everybody’s Prickly Pear 12oz
Description: Flavor that has strawberry, watermelon, honeydew, and fig

Name: Deschutes The Ages 500ml
Description: Gueze-inspired, multi-year blending shapes a wild brew brimming with fruity, spicy esters and savory, tangy pear and white pepper flavors.

Name: Little Beast Dream State/Golden Stone 375ml
Description: Strawberry

Name: The Brewing Projekt Pineapp-Cherruava Puff 16oz
Description: Kettle Sour with milk sugar, cherry, pineapple, guava and marshmallow.

Name: Ja-pas Matsu-rika 16oz
Description: One of the highlights of Japanese cuisine is the tea. And one of the most delicate and flavorful Asian teas is made using the jasmine petals, called Matsurika in Japan. We added these petals to the recipe of a Pilsen, a soft and delicate beer, bringing floral notes to the aroma and palate.

Name: Ja-pas Sawa Yuzu 16oz
Description: Com a acidez característica do estilo, leve e refrescante, Sawa é a tradução para "Sour" em japonês. A base perfeita para uma cerveja que, nesta versão, leva yuzu, um cítrico japonês de acidez acentuada e extremamente aromático, lembrando uma mistura de limão siciliano, tangerina e toranja. Essa Sour também leva os lúpulos Citra e Cascade no dry hopping, potencializando ainda mais as características cítricas dessa fruta tão rara.

Name: Ja-pas Shukuirmu 16oz
Description: Matcha is a special green tea made from the sprouts of camellia sinensis grounded in stone mill. Much appreciated in Asian cuisine for its flavor and color, it is used in desserts such as Shukurimu, the Japanese version of French Choux Cream. This beer is our interpretation of this pastry: a combination of matcha and vanilla with the creaminess of flaked wheat and oats, finishing with massive amounts of hops.

Name: Skookum Caverns 16oz
Description: Barrel aged and Blended strong ale. 40% old ale aged in Heaven Hill barrels, and 60% imperial oatmeal brown ale aged in Basil Hayden barrels.

Name: Hair Of The Dog Bourbon Fred 12oz
Brewery: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
Description: Bourbon Fred From The Wood is my regular Fred, aged for over a year in Kentucky bourbon barrels. Released in bottles in 2011. Alcohol: 12% by volume.

Name: Seattle Marionberry 16oz
Description: The most popular varietal of blackberries in the Pacific Northwest, Marionberries share their pleasant tartiness and complex flavors in a cider that is sure to delight

Name: Drekker Underwater Ally 16oz
Description: Underwater Ally was brewed with a bunch of oats & spelt, then hopped with Mosaic, Citra, and Ella for a super tropical, citrus, and grapefruity flavor & aroma. <U+2800>

Name: Drekker Tickle Monster 16oz
Description: Tickle Monster is a Double IPA brewed with Lactose Sugar and Belma & Mosaic hops. No monsters were harmed (or tickled) in the making of this beer.

Name: Evasion Hophoria 12oz
Description: A Euphoric blend of Mosaic and Citra hops that burst with stonefruit and citrus fruit notes. With a well balanced malt body.

Name: Ruse Phantom Shore 16oz
Description: American style extra pale ale brewed exclusively with Citra hops.

Name: Little Beast Czech-Style Pilsner 16oz
Description: A simple and true-to-style lager, brewed with Bohemian malt and Czech-grown Saaz hops. Toasted biscuit and bready malt flavors, a classic spicy hop character, and a refreshingly crisp finish.

Name: North Coast Pranqster 12oz
Description: Belgian Ales represent the height of the brewers' art. Sophisticated brewing techniques, yeast blends and unique flavoring elements have elevated the beers of Belgium to the status enjoyed by wine in other countries.

Name: Masthead Flat Earth 16oz
Description: We threw brewing science to the curb with this beer and added an unbelievably stupid amount of hops at every step of the process. Logic and reason need not apply. Just stop reading this, believe us that it's good, and drink it already.

Name: Henhouse Juiced 16oz
Description: So much raspberry puree from Oregon Fruit Products up in this batch of our juiced accompanied by the most sensational sea salt addition! Bright notes of raspberry jam, sour straws, and slight salinity making this here beer oh so delightful!

Name: Topa Topa Spectro 12oz
Description: Tasting Notes: pineapple, grapefruit, guava

Name: Old Nation B-43 16oz
Description: B-43 uses the same recipe hops as M-43 but no residual sugar, 3g of carbs per pint, and 7%!

Name: Claim 52 Bird Up 16oz
Description: Strawberry Milkshake IPA

Name: Temescal Hazy IPA 16oz
Description: Temescal Hazy strikes the right balance of flaked oats and malted wheat creating a lush, fluffy mouthfeel that’s not too heavy. Packed with Mosaic, Simcoe and Citra hops--this is our essential Hazy IPA.

Name: Temescal Pils 16oz
Description: A crisp and refreshing Pilsner with pleasant herbal notes from the noble hop, subtle floral esters from a beautiful Lager yeast, and a splash of honeysuckle from the finest German malts.

Name: Boss Rambler Cold One 16oz
Description: Cold, light, and crushable. Your drink it anytime, drink it all the time Cold One!

Name: Boss Rambler Dude Cruise 16oz
Description: Double Dry-Hopped w/ Centennial, Chinook, and Citra

Name: Black Project Kipper 16oz
Description: Sour Wheat ale with Pineapple and Pomegranate

Name: Chapman Timeless Beauty 16oz
Description: A classic West Coast style IPA hopped with Cascade, Citra, Amarillo and Chinook. Citrus, pine, resin.

Name: Bearded Iris Double Scatterbrain 16oz
Description: We took our Double Scatterbrain, already heavily hopped with Simcoe and double dry-hopped it with Citra. This beer is bursting with passionfruit, grapefruit and pine.

Name: Bearded Iris Double Homestyle 16oz
Description: The soft and juicy Mosaic of Homestyle in a crushably smooth 8.2% body.

Name: Hop Capital Brewing Hazepocalypse 12oz
Description: Hops (Citra, Mosaic, El Dorado)

Name: Brewing Projekt Big Shooter 16oz
Description: Double India Pale Ale with Citra, Mosaic, Sabro and Honey

Name: Barlows Mountain Spectre 16oz
Description: Brocken Spectre, also called Mountain Spectre, is the magnified shadow of an observer cast upon the clouds opposite the Sun's direction. This hazy IPA is hopped with a Mountain Mosaic and Simcoe hops. (Juicy tropical, Citrus Zest)

Name: Barlows Alpina 16oz
Description: A Vienna Lager that is crisp and refreshing. Brewed with Hersbrucker hops that add a subtle fruity aroma with a nice malty backbone to give this beer a classic Viennese finish.

Name: Barlows Crispy Mitts 16oz
Description: A Canadian Lager that is a crisp, light and refreshing. Brewed with 100% Canadian malts and German Hersbrucker hops.

Name: Crux Bubble Wrap 12oz
Description: In pursuit of the next great Hazy IPA, safety is not guaranteed. To craft this highly drinkable adaptation of the style, we evaded all the murky, mysterious gimmicks in favor of a balanced body of flaked oats and wheat accompanied by whole leaf Citra, Mosaic, and Galaxy hops popping with juicy, tropical flavors. Dangerously delicious, this hazy drinks clean and keeps you coming back for more.

Name: Flatland Dream Clouds 16oz
Description: •Dream Clouds - Hazy DIPA w/ Citra, Strata, Galaxy 8%

Name: Equilibrium Juice^2 16oz
Description: Triple IPA brewed in collaboration with our friends at Equilibrium Brewing in NY. Dry hopped with Citra and Galaxy hops.

Name: Equilibrium Fluctuation Wave 16oz
Description: Fluctuation Wave takes our beloved DIPA Fluctuation, supersizes the hop bill, adds a touch of lactose, and uses our revised hop process. The tasting notes for this are simple: This beer is the DIPA version of Straight Outta The Laboratory with even more EQ juice and a smooth lactose finish. We’re very excited about this one.

Name: Surly Rocket Surgery 12oz
Description: This juicy, hazy ale is brimming with Citra and Simcoe hops for a fruit-forward blast of hop flavor. Drink it. You’ll like it. It’s not rocket surgery, it's Rocket Surgery.

Name: Surly Hell 16oz
Description: Hell is German for "light." A pale gold lager with bready malt aromas and flavors, floral hop aroma, and a balanced finish.

Name: Double Mountain Dry Cider 500ml
Description: Dry Hopped Pale Ale

Name: Anderson Valley Old Fashioned 12oz
Description: Inspired by our love for the classic bourbon cocktail, this robust brown ale is brewed with orange peel and Hersbrucker hops, which naturally have orange-like flavors. Fresh cherry

Name: Caldera Pale Ale 12oz
Description: A West Coast-Style Pale Ale balancing plenty of hops with a malty backbone. Cascade Hops. Malts: Premium Two Row, Light Munich, Crystal. 5.6 ABV. 55 IBU

Name: Tieton Apricot 12oz
Description: When we infuse our crisp apple cider with the tartness of apricot, the apple flavor decreases and the apricot notes shine; you will taste both fresh and dried apricot. Enjoy this cider on its own or balance the concentrated acid with blue or soft goat cheese.

Name: Bruery Gypsy Tart 750ml
Description: Gypsy Tart is a Flanders-style brown ale, with a California touch. A beer that can trace it's origins to Great Britain, but more famously perfected in western Belgium, has been updated through our own modern techniques, delivering the sweet body and mildly tart finish that has won over numerous generations of beer drinkers in Europe. Our rendition of this wonderful beer style is perfect for both sour beer amateurs and advocates alike.

Name: Stormbreaker Helter Shelter
Description: West Coast IPA w/ Summit, Chinook, Cascade and dry hopped Azacca, Strata, Cashmere hops

Name: Illuminated Orange Sunshine
Description: Melt your face on this deliciously dry citrus Saison built for long days irradiating under the evil star.

Name: Brouwerij West Popfuji 16oz
Description: Our take on the historic Kellerbier, Popfuji Unfiltered Pilsner delivers a delicate malt sweetness combined with a subtle fruit and spice character from the use of German Noble Hops. Unlike the typical Pilsner, however, Popfuji's uniqueness is in it's smooth, creamy texture, making it perfect for any occasion.

Name: Brouwerij West Supercollider 16oz
Description: The worlds of JUICY and DANK collide! The aftermath fuses flavors of tropical fruits, bright berries, and earthy pine straight upon your mouth mantle. The combination of Citra, Mosaic, and Motueka Hops leaves you pondering the vast possibilities of the hop universe, while a blend of malted and raw barley, with raw oats, leaves every sip feeling like your tongue is in zero gravity.

Name: Belching Beaver Buenos Tiempos 16oz
Description: Mexican-style lager.

Name: Thunder Island Pet Rock And A Moon Boot 16oz
Description: This beer has an irresponsible amount of hops in it. Juicy is the goal, haze is the byproduct. The Citra, Mosaic, and Mandarina Bavaria hops paired with a very expressive New England yeast strain really bring the juice on.

Name: Thunder Island Remember The Forrest 16oz
Description: Conceived during the fires in the Columbia River Gorge as our Head Brewer stood outside watching some of his favorite trails burst into flames. While creating Remember the Forest IPA our brewers continued on in the direction of less is more. By keeping the malt and hop bill low the goal is to deliver a clean, tasty, floral IPA. This beer contains Simcoe, Amarillo, and Mosaic hops to deliver a balance of piney and citrus flavors.

Name: Trap Door Saint Pablo 16oz
Description: Mexican-Style Lager with Motueka hops for a subtle lime aroma. Super crushable and refreshing for the summer months!

Name: Everybody’s Brewing Velvet Tiger IPA 16oz
Description: Northwest-style Double IPA w/ Simcoe, Chinook and Cascade hops.

Name: Revision IPA
Description: Brewed with our legendary Burton water. Palate of biscuit malt, spicy hops and light fruitiness. Now with added personality.

Name: The Bruery Sour In The Rye
Description: Sour in the Rye is an American wild ale. A challenging beer to brew due to the substantial amount of rye malt, but you’ll be glad we took the time. The character of the rye asserts itself with clove and pepper in the aroma and flavor, and contributes a full body not generally found in sour beers. Pleasantly sour with notes of tart cherry, rustic earth and vanilla from barrel aging.

Name: Mountains Walking Twisted Karma 16oz
Description: The Twisted Karma is a pleasantly tart and refreshing sour beer which bursts at the seams with bushels of real raspberries. This intensely red, tart and quenchable beer is loaded with flavor that will leave you wanting another.

Name: Mountains Walking Tin Sky 16oz
Description: Hazy New England IPA with copious Dry-Hop additions of VIc Secret and Mosaic. Stonefruit JUICE!!!

Name: Mountains Walking Opaque thoughts 16oz
Description: Opaque Thoughts is our Milkshake IPA Series. The first flavor out of the gate on this series is Guava. This NEIPA is brewed with an extreme amount of toasted rice flakes, oats, wheat and lactose before being conditioned on the perfect amount of Guava puree and Papa New Guinea Vanilla Bean. We then dry-hopped this with a ridiculously delicious combination of Mosaic, Hallertau Blanc and Strata at nearly 6lbs per barrel.

Name: BUOY PILS
Description: Bright traditional taste. A classic pilsner with roots in the great beer heritage of the Czech Republic. Our Czech-Style Pilsner features Saaz hops supporting layers of rounded malt flavors. As right today as it was a few hundred years ago. From a place that’s weathered a few trends in its time; here, history never gets old.

Name: The Bruery Rueuze 750ml
Description: Humulus Rueuze is a variation on our take on the traditional Belgian-style lambic gueuze with one major exception: massive amounts of dry hops. To begin, we carefully selected a number of oak barrels that have been aging our sour blonde ale anywhere from several months to several years, and then blended the beers together for the ideal flavor profile. In this 2016 edition, we then piled heaps of Huell Melon hops on top to achieve an aromatic blend like no other, inundating the senses with fruity, melon and strawberry notes. This is one complex beer, and it’s best consumed fresh.

Name: Fort George Optimist 12oz
Description: Sometimes it’s hard to look on the bright side of life, but The Optimist will keep your spirits aloft. Simplicity being the ultimate in sophistication, we use a very concise recipe in this India Pale Ale to showcase the providential union of barley and hops. With its radiant golden body, a lively buoyant head and auspicious floral aroma your glass will always be half-full while drinking The Optimist.

Name: Hair Of The Dog Blue Dot 16oz
Brewery: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
Description: Blue Dot is named after our planet: we are only a pale blue dot in this universe. Made with Organic Pilsner malt, Rye malt and a combination of intense hop varieties. Pour slowly to allow the sediments to remain in the bottle. Make every day Earth Day. Be something nice for your mother.

Name: MikkellerSD Træblod 16oz
Description: Imperial stout brewed w/ maple syrup & coffee

Name: Block 15 Oaked Maibock 16oz
Description: Brewed with specialty European malts and fermented cold with German lager yeast, our Maibock melds alluring malt notes of honey, caramelized sugar, dried fruit, and freshly baked bread. Conditioning in oak casks layered on subtle notes of vanilla and oak.

Name: Dssolvr Bloomin In The Juicy 16oz
Description: 'Bloomin' in the Juicy' marks the return of our Juicy series, depicting the life cycle of our brand...through creepy illustrations of head brewer Vince. This one is a big DIPA, packed with a very wide plethora of Oats and Wheat, then loaded to the brim with Mosaic and Crystal hops, along with an extreme amount of Hibiscus in the whirlpool for an extra fruity-tooty character. We flipped the script and pummelled it with even more Mosaic and a heaping pile of Amarillo in the dry-hop, along with an equally extreme amount of Hibiscus. Fruity as all get-out, this is gonna make you rip that scoot’ on down the block, bust a grind or two, and impress the whole crew. It won't give you wings, but it might make you more radical ??.

Name: Dssolvr Tv Wasteland 16oz
Description: Old World Pilsner

Name: Dssolvr Thank You For Existing 16oz
Description: Kölsch Style Ale featuring Crystal, Huell Melon, and Saphir hops

Name: Weldwerks Juicy Bits 16oz
Description: Our flagship IPA features a huge citrus and tropical fruit hop character from the Mosaic, Citra & El Dorado hops and softer, smoother mouthfeel from the adjusted water chemistry, higher protein malts, and lower attenuation. The end result is a beer reminiscent of citrus juice with extra pulp, thus the name Juicy Bits.

Name: Unsung Brewing Shatter Spike 16oz
Description: West Coast IPA with Citra and Mosaic. “With a burst of Citra & Mosaic hop flavor, Shatterspike takes no prisoners. Once its arsenal of aroma has sunk into your palate, you’ll find it nearly impossible to escape.”

Name: Alvarado Street Motor Oil 16oz
Description: Our incredibly decadent, rich & roasty Imperial Stout treated with white chocolate in the form of raw cacao butter, Ecuadorian cacao nibs, Tahitian vanilla, & a generous addition of raspberry.

Name: Alvarado Street Good N Fresh Ipa 16oz
Description: A name that's all about what we preach; the fresher the better when it comes to hoppy beer. This "Westy" is no exception, and it's brewed with one of the most elusive hops out there - Riwaka from New Zealand. Known for it's sauvignon blanc-like tropical bouquet with a bit of sticky diesel, we've paired it up with freshly harvested, super punchy 2019 Strata from Oregon.

Name: Henhouse IPA 16oz
Description: HenHouse IPA is the sun at the center of our hoppy beer solar system and its gravity keeps everything else rotating nicely. Making this beer year round allows us to travel to hop farms every harvest and select the lots of those key hops that meet our exacting standards for maximum deliciousness. Built around five of our most favoritest hops: Cascade, Simcoe, Mosaic, Belma and Hallertau Blanc, all of our hoppy beer flows through what this beer has allowed us to do - it’s our keystone and it’s always hella fresh!

Name: Aslan Batch 15 12oz
Description: This hoppy creation is everything a Northwest IPA should be. It showcases the amazing resinous and piney characteristics of Simcoe, the crisp citrus of Citra, and the bitterness of Summit hops. Pouring a beautiful opaque orange, this beer is juicy, unfiltered, and delicious!

Name: Allegory Dad Hat 16oz
Description: 2019 Best of Craft Gold Medal Winner.

Name: Occidental Pilsner
Description: Occidental's take on the lager style that changed the beer world forever. This is a largely Bohemian-style pilsner with a bit of a Bavarian pedigree. Crisp, clean and dry. Czech hops crown this beautiful beer.

Name: Ecliptic Ruse Pilsner 16oz
Description: Brewed with our friends at Ruse Brewing, this Italian-style Pilsner is generously dry-hopped with all German hops, including Polaris, Saphir and Hallertau Blanc.

Name: Left Hand Chai Milk Stout/Gettin Tiki With It 16oz
Skookum Gene Pool 16oz
Description: Gene Pool is brewed with a simple grist of pale malt and flaked rye. Generously hopped with Mosiac, Simcoe and Nugget hops throughout the brew process. Sticky-dank flavors and aromas abound in this one. Come get some! 8% abv.

Name: Jolly Pumpkin Bam Biere 16oz
Description: An artisan farmhouse ale that is golden, naturally cloudy, bottle conditioned and dry hopped for a perfectly refreshing balance of spicy malts, hops and yeast.

Name: Breakside Portland IPA 16oz
Description: Back to the Future IPA, our cross-border collaboration with Seattle’s Fremont Brewing, is the Official Beer of Portland Beer Week! Join us for the Bottle Release Party on June 12th from 5pm – 8pm at Whole Foods Market in the Pearl (1210 NW Couch St,, Portland, OR 97209). We’ll have two versions of the Back to the Future IPA on tap, alongside Fremont’s Summer Ale and our Old World IPA.

Name: Grains Of Wrath Built For Speed 16oz
Description: Our head brewer Mike Hunsaker has had this recipe in his pocket for a while. Light and dry with flavors of tropical fruit, pine and dank grapefruit. Drinks like an old friend.

Name: Sasquatch Woodboy 16oz
Description: A West Coast IPA with big stone fruit and piney flavors dry hopped with loads of citras. This region grows the best hops in the world, so a true Oregon IPA has to let them shine. We keep Woodboy surprisingly light in body to allow the centennial, cascade, and citra hops to stand out in every sip. The finish is all dank pine and tropical fruit and the head stands firm, dense and bright white.

Name: Level Rocket Surgery/Low Resolution/Stable/brewbin
Description: Hazy IPA with a bunch of hops and easy drink flavors! Made with Nelson Sauvin, Vic Secret, El Dorado, and a super fun Experimental variety!

Name: Masthead Jalapeño 16oz
Description: Brewed with fresh jalapeños, the fruity notes from hand-selected hops pair well with that unmistakable aroma and flavor, all backed up with just the right level of spiciness.

Name: Wayfinder CZAF 16oz
Description: DECOCTED PILSNER

Name: Ruse Pilsner 16oz
Description: Brewed with our friends at Ruse Brewing, this Italian-style Pilsner is generously dry-hopped with all German hops, including Polaris, Saphir and Hallertau Blanc.

Name: Urban Roots EZPZ 16oz
Description: Dry hopped pilsner

Name: Baerlic Dad Beer/Chill/myld/ You And Me/Dream Life
Description: Brewed with flaked corn reminiscent of your great great grandpappy’s favorite chuggin’ beer from the 1880s but with notes of ripe fruit, fresh spring flowers and a touch of citrus in a beer made for drinkin’!

Name: Urban Roots Nothing Can Stop
Description: DDH Unfiltered DIPA w/ Citra, Strata and Galaxy.

Name: Block 15 Mexican Lager 16oz
Description: Our Mexican-style dark lager balances a delicate blend of caramelly, nutty, and toasty malt notes with crisp minerality and an earthy, lemony lager yeast character. It is fermented cool and conditioned cold, smoothing out the finish on this dry, refreshing lager.

Name: Firestone Walker Mind Haze 12oz
Description: From the coast of California comes Mind Haze, a free-spirited beer made to elevate your perceptions—juicy yet balanced, hazy yet lasting, and loaded with an imaginative array of tropical hop flavors.

Name: Grains Of Wrath Crypt Keeper 16oz
Description: Single Hop Citra. Bright. Citrus. Lime. Tropical.

Name: Block 15 Fresca Pils 16oz
Description: A crisp, hop-forward Italian-style pilsner brewed with Italian Eraclea pilsner malt and generously hopped with European Styrian hops, lending zippy notes of citrus, berries, and fresh-cut grass. designed in cooperation with label artist Chris Herbst of Ashland’s Flow Factory NW.

Name: Block 15 Nebula
Description: An imperial variation of our classic oat stout Nebula, matured in bourbon barrels and conditioned with fresh roasted cocoa nibs.

Name: Boneyard Hop Venom
Description: A classic West Coast imperial IPA, it’s big and malty, yet surprisingly balanced.

Name: Sierra Nevada Barrel Aged Narwhal 16oz
Description: Barrel-Aged Narwhal is our deliciously dark Imperial Stout aged in Kentucky bourbon barrels. Barrel aging is a strange science; it mellows some characteristics of the original beer while intensifying others. Narwhal’s aggressive roastiness has calmed, but the rich, chocolate-like malt backbone is brought to the fore. Black as midnight, this intense stout is complex with notes of cocoa and espresso balanced with hints of vanilla and toasted coconut from the oak casks. Nearly as rare as it’s nautical namesake, try Barrel-Aged Narwhal while you can because like the creature itself, it will soon dive into the depths and leave nary a trace behind.

Name: Boulevard Tank 7 16oz
Description: A traditional Belgian-style farmhouse ale, the perfect combination of elements came together in their #7 fermenter. You could call it fate, but they called it Tank 7, and so it is. Beginning with a big surge of fruity aromatics and grapefruit-hoppy notes, the flavor of this complex, straw-colored ale tapers off to a peppery, dry finish.

Name: Brewing Projekt Double Dare Mighty Things 16oz
Drake’s Cult Of The Sun 500ml
Description: Starting out as a mixed culture sour blonde ale, Cult of the Sun is aged for over a year in Zinfandel Barrels and infused with a healthy dose of California Yuzu and Buddhas Hand Citron. Unique, juicy, bright and floral, this brew is worthy of a cult following.

Name: Ecliptic Fifth Orbit/Star Party/Cosmos/Sedna/Oort 500ml
Description: Ecliptic 5th anniversary. Dry-Hopped Strawberry Sour Ale was brewed with real strawberries. Belma, Mosaic, Chinook, Cascade, and Simcoe hops complement the fruit notes. Dry-hopped strawberry sour ale

Name: Tø Øl Secret Santa 500ml
Beer: Santa’s Secret: Mochaccino Messiah Double Shot
Description: Ever wondered how other Christmas delivers presents down al of those chimneys in one night? Well he may have a little help up his sleeve. Santas Secret is our classic Moccachino Messiah – and some. Injected full of coffee, this 8% beauty is both sweet and malty with hints of chocolate, a boost of caffeine and warm Christmas notes of Cinnamon and Cardamom to finish of. He is Scandinavian after all.

Name: Alesong 2018 Rhino Suit 500ml
Description: Matured in freshly emptied Heaven Hill bourbon barrels.

Name: Level Game On IPA 12oz
Description: Light body with a mild maltiness, big juicy hop aroma, lots of hoppy flavor balanced by a moderate bitterness. Big citrus and pine.

Name: Migration Mohazeic
Description: Loaded with passion fruit, papaya, orange and tropical aromas. Highlighting Mosaic, Amarillo, Citra, and Wakatu hops.

Name: Stormbreaker Savage Nimbus 16oz
Description: Brewed with the extreme hop lover in mind. Yeah...YOU! The nose starts off with sweet tangerine and a touch of grapefruit with hints of floral and spicy hops. Up front maltiness on the palate quickly yields to spice, pine and citrus, with a savagely hoppy finish for all of you hop heads out there.

Name: Jolly Pumpkin Calabaza Blanca 16oz
Description: Calabaza Blanca is a low-calorie farmhouse white ale brewed in Belgium's bière blanche tradition. Spiced with orange peel and coriander, you'll find it refreshingly tart, with a wonderfully dry finish. A year-round favorite for sure!

Name: Lagunitas Seasonal 12oz
Description: This is our unique version of an ancient style. A style as old as the ocean trade routes of the last centuries Great Ships. Not as old as the equator they had to cross twice enroute.

Name: Stormbreaker Mississippi Red 16oz
Description: An homage to our street we now call home, this Citra dry hopped Red gives the appearance of an IPA on the nose, with hops apparent on the palate, but balanced with caramel flavors for a smooth finish. Red perfection!

Name: Stickmen Orxata/Paddle 16oz
Description: This milk stout was brewed with oats and rice and spiked with cinnamon, almond, and vanilla for a horchata experience.

Name: Ex Novo Kill The Sun 16oz
Description: Bourbon BBL Aged Stout releases annually during winter.

Name: Wolves & People Tractor Pull 16.9oz
Description: Our medium-bodied, aromatic, dry-hopped pale ale is loaded with lush and tropical hop character. Not quite an IPA, but more pungent than a typical pale ale. Juicy with aromas of citrus and stone fruit.

Name: Dogfish Head Fruitfull Fort 12oz
Description: A twist on our beloved Fort, Fruit-Full Fort is brewed with four types of berries - raspberry, blackberry, boysenberry and elderberry. This juicy blend of dark berries creates depth and complexity reminiscent of a jammy red wine.

Name: Baerlic Woodworker Night Howler/Perpetual Astonishment 2019 500ml
Description: We took our tasty roasty delicious imperial stout and through it into the perfect compliment of charred oak & caramel from still wet 8+ year old Bookers bourbon casks.

Name: North Coast Barrel Aged Rasputin XVII
Beer: Rye Whiskey Barrel Aged Old Rasputin XVIII
Description: Every year we age a special batch of our much-loved Russian Imperial Stout in Bourbon barrels. The depth, intensity, and complexity of the flavor profile of this special release, like its predecessors, make it a worthy tribute to Old Rasputin. This year, two variants of barrel aged Old Rasputin were produced -- one in rye whiskey barrels, and the other in wheat whiskey barrels. ABV: 11.3%

Name: Against The Grain Gnight Ryder 750ml
Description: Aged in red wine barrels. No beer is above the law around here, including Gnight Ryder. This imperial black ale is interred in red wine barrels and emerges unrecognizable. It’s not the general, it sure ain’t the sheriff, it’s the Gnight Ryder.

Name: Moylan’s Old Blanery Barleywine
Description: HUGE malt flavors with big hop kick.

Name: Sierra Nevada 2015 BA Narwahl
Description: Imperial stout aged in Kentucky bourbon barrels.

Name: Crux All Worked Up 500ml
Description: There’s no substitute for brewing things right, and the 6 months of patience as this rare breed blossomed in the barrel was the least of our endeavors to deliver this no-frills interpretation of an American wheatwine. This labor-intensive strong ale delivers delicate notes of candied fruit, caramel, and vanilla with a well-rounded mouthfeel worth getting all worked up over.

Name: Rev Nat’s Blend
Description: Revival begins simply: select the best whole apples in the world, grind them up and cold press them, just like farmers do every harvest. Then I add Dark Muscovado, an unrefined cane juice grown in Mauritius. This blend of cane and apple juices is fermented to complete dryness using a Belgian saison ale yeast (producing round and creamy mouthfeel) and an exotic secret strain carefully managed to give waves of pineapple, guava and peach flavors. Back-sweetened with fresh apple juice, never from concentrate. Brilliantly golden in color and deeply complex while remaining subtly familiar, with just the right amount of sweetness and acidity to be an everyday beverage, this cider represents the culmination of my 10 years of cider making.

Name: Ale Apothecary Sahati 750ml
Description: SAHATI is our interpretation of traditional Finnish sahti. Starting with a 200-year old Engelmann spruce tree felled on brewery property, we created our own kuurna (an ancient Scandinavian lauter tun) to separate the wort from the grain during brewing. The bottom of the kuurna is layered with spruce branches; the needles act as a natural filter and impart resinous oils into the wort. The hollowed-out trunk of the tree also contributes spruce essence and structure from the raw wood. The beer is made of barley & rye malts along with a sparing addition of Goschie Farms Cascade hops and is brewed just a few times per year.? SAHATI is in many ways the very definition of The Ale Apothecary, where complex flavors arrive from the very methods used for production…the result is the process impacts the flavor profile at least as much as the ingredients themselves.

Name: Brothers Cascadia Lydian 500ml
Description: “The First beers ever composed and brewed at Brothers Cascadia were designed to be aged in barrels and blended into our first sour beers. This mixed culture ale combines qualities of raspberry jam and a balanced acidity that leads you through a melody worth enjoying now and for years to come.”

Name: Ommegang Three Philosophers
Description: Rich and complex, this tour de force is a glorious blend of elegant Belgian-style quadruple ale and authentic Belgian kriek, its malty depth and gentle sweetness enhanced by sparkling carbonation and a serendipitous touch of cherry.

Name: Drakes Island Diaries
Description: Find your way back to paradise with our version of a Caribbean nightcap. Notes of coconut, banana bread, and rum spice meld beautifully with the mild caramel and the coffee-like backbone in this beer. Sip, savor, and get away from it all with Rum Diaries.

Name: Varietal Nectarina
Description: This farmhouse ale was brewed with Washington-grown Purple Egyptian & Scots Bere heritage barley, then refermented with Brett & 400lbs of Sunnyside-grown Upland Farms nectarines.

Name: Great Divide Strawberry Rhubarb 12oz
Description: Strawberry Rhubarb Sour is a gift for the senses. Strawberry is the yin to rhubarb’s yang—the sweet to the tart. This beautiful partnership creates a beer that glows ruby in the glass, bursts with strawberry aroma, and bites with every sip. Bright and effervescent, this sour is a fun and refreshing, lip-puckering treat perfect for every occasion, any time of the year.

Name: Crooked Stave 2015 Serenata Notturna
Description: Belgian style golden ale aged in oak casks

Name: Urban Roots Luna De Miel 16oz
Description: Vienna/Mexican Amber Lager brewed with Weyermann(R) Pils, Vienna and Caramunich malts. Smooth easy drinking amber lager.

Name: Kulmbacher Eisbock 11.2oz
Description: Last vintage of Reichelbrau Eisbock

Name: Aecht Schlenkerla Helles Marzen 16oz
Description: In the world of German brewing, Kräusen refers to the intense proliferation of bubbles and foam formed during fermentation of a young or “green” beer. And Aufkräusen (literally to kräusen it up), refers to a historic brewing technique in which some green beer is added to a fully-matured lager. This is a very old and very typically German tradition, and today even English-speaking brewers refer to this technique as krausening. Krausening brings the vibrant freshness of young beer to the more refined, austere flavors of a fully-matured lager.

Name: Marble 2014 Reserve Ale 22oz
Description: Aged in bourbon barrels.

Name: PERENNIAL SUMP
Description: Non-barrel aged Sump Stout. Imperial Stout blended with Sump Coffee

Name: New West Sweet Tea 16oz
Description: A sacred southern tradition with a northwest twist. Traditional Georgian sweet made with Oregon peaches. Sweet and thirst-quenching. Steeped hot and served ice cold.

Name: Coldfire Kite String IPA 16oz
Description: The Kite String IPA is our tribute to all that is beautiful with the West Coast IPA. Old school hops meet newer, juicy, tropical varieties in the delicious, refreshing homage to our roots.

Name: Komes Raspberry Porter 500ml
Description: 21°Blg

Name: Chang Classic Beer 620ml
Description: Contents from fine quality malt, rice, and hop, with natural water, and selected yeast, especially for Chang Beer. Brewed at 1. Cosmos Brewery (Thailand) Co. Ltd. 2. Beer Thip Brewery (1991) Co., Ltd. 3. Beer Thai (1991) Plc.

Name: Rodenbach Fruitage 11oz
Description: Rodenbach FruitAge is a blend of aged ale, young ale and 9% red fruit, which gives it its sweet-sourness and fruity notes. Pure refreshment.

Name: Great Divide Woodwerks 12oz
Beer: Wood Werks Barrel Series #3: Imperial Rye Brown
Description: Aged in 10-year rye whiskey barrels for over 13 months, this imperial brown rye ale was brewed with copious amounts of malted and flaked rye, accentuating spicy and bready notes. The complex malt bill, paired with spirited characteristics from the aging process, makes for a smooth and full-bodied finish.

Name: Trinity Koelorado
Description: Brewed with a first and second 'slims' process, a malt bill consisting of over 30% raw wheat, and aged hops. A 'first of its kind' beer to be produced in Colorado, in which we push the hot wort outside to our custom built coolship overnight allowing indigenous Colorado microbes to blow in and ferment the beer. Staying very strict to Belgian tradition, we only brew this beer during March and April when wild microbes are most favorable. This beer then ages for a full year on steam sterilized French oak Chardonnay barrels before bottling.

Name: Leffe Blonde
Description: In the fifties, an extraordinary meeting took place that all beer enthusiasts should raise their glass of Leffe to. <U+2028> The abbey’s Father Abbot Nys became acquainted with Albert Lootvoet, a master brewer.<U+2028> Passionate about the future of the brewery, Father Nys was upset to have to witness how, since the unpleasant stay of the French revolutionaries, the brewery had slowly fallen into decline and had eventually had to close its doors in 1809. Such a magnificent place could not be forgotten, he believed, and he vowed to bring the Leffe beer back. Father Nys and the brewer set about the challenge with vigour…and succeeded. Shortly after, the Leffe brewery was back in full effect. After Leffe Brown, a beer that shone brighter than the sun saw the light of day; they named it Leffe Blond – a beautiful chapter for Leffe indeed.

Name: ROCHEFORT 6
Description: Rochefort 6 (red cap, brown beer, 7.5% ABV). Reddish colour, brewed only about once per year, representing approximately 1% of total beer production. This beer begins with a density of 16.5º Plato is 7.5% ABV. “Rochefort 6” is the oldest Rochefort Trappist beer, and was brewed empirically until the end of the Second World War. Until 1958, this was the only Rochefort beer that was bottled in both 33 cc bottles and 75 cc bottles. It has a strong malt taste and is slightly bitter.

Name: Upright Saison Vert 375ml
Description: Made with black limes for both a citric and earthy character. The lightly spicy yeast notes and dry finish contrast a creamy wheat base, making it a nuanced yet quaffable brew.

Name: Beachwood Into Great Unknown
Description: a dry-hopped lambic-inspired ale in which we utilize a different hop varietal for each batch. We begin by carefully selecting and blending barrels that have been aging for 9 to 14 months. Then, once the desired combination is chosen, we dry hop in the blending tank with a specific variety of hops (in this version, Mosaic), and bottle condition with wine yeast for at least three months. In this first rendition of Into the Great Unknown, the aromas of tropical fruit from the hops work seamlessly to accentuate the funk and acidity of the underlying blend.

Name: Beachwood Chaos Is A Friend Of Mine 375ml
Beer: Chaos Is A Friend of Mine
Description: ‘Chaos is a Friend of Mine’ is the result of blending barrels of our base beer to produce the flavor profile of a Belgian Lambic. We begin with a traditional grain bill composed of pilsner malt and raw wheat, which is then boiled for an extended amount of time with aged hops. The wort is then fermented and aged in neutral French oak barrels with our diverse house culture. Chaos ensues from the countless strains of yeast and bacteria fighting for dominance, and after 9 - 14 months in the barrel, we introduce the power of blending to bring order back, ultimately creating a beer that's greater than the sum of its parts. Funk takes center stage in this brew, with notes of barnyard, stone fruit, and aged hops. A balanced and clean acidity make this beer tart, yet extremely palatable, with a full body and crisp dry finish.

Name: Jackie O’s Nectar Flow 500ml
Description: Honey Saison aged for 33 months in wine barrels

Name: Frecon Brix 12oz
Description: A crisp blend of sweet and sharp apples styled slightly off dry. It's our first ever sweet cider. It's sweet for us and in the traditional artisanal cider sense. We used a unique filtering process to maintain a gorgeous natural color. The end result is a beautiful cider that goes down smooth and leaves a taste of fresh delicious apples right out of the orchard.

Name: Die Hochland Winter Mead 500ml
Description: Sweet mead with Vanilla pods, cinnamon, cloves, and nutmeg.

Name: Firestone Walker Cherry Barrel Blossom 12oz
Description: Imperial Porter aged in bourbon barrels for one year and six to eight months in cherry bitters barrels. The final blend is 88% bourbon barrel-aged beer mixed with 12% cherry bitters barrel-aged beer. The bourbon and cherry bitters barrels give the beer aromas and flavors of cherry, bourbon, vanilla, tobacco and milk chocolate.

Name: Firestone Walker Mind Haze 19oz
Description: From the coast of California comes Mind Haze, a free-spirited beer made to elevate your perceptions—juicy yet balanced, hazy yet lasting, and loaded with an imaginative array of tropical hop flavors.

Name: Brewing Projekt Hyperspace 16oz
Description: Hazy IPA brewed w/ Mosaic, Simcoe, & Idaho 7 hops.

Name: Evil Twin Excuse Me French Toast 16oz
Beer: Excuse Me, Do You Speak French Toast?
Description: Imperial Stout with Maple & Cinnamon

Name: Hoof Hearted $60 Nachos 16oz
Description: $60 Nachos? That’s what happens when you let dad outta the house!

Name: Nightmare Crucifixion 16oz
Description: DIPA w/ Sacramental Bread, Calypso, Vic Secret & Simcoe

Name: Hoof Hearted Stackin Paper 16oz
Description: The silk has been spun & the oil refinied. Look past the mind & into the third eye. 10lbs per bbl of galaxy tend blood from the unwilling to be let again. Was Hoofyman really first to the moon? Ancient secrets secrete like primordial ooze. Stackin paper so sticky you'd swear it was honey. You keep the cases, we're taking your money.

Name: Oozlefinch Twangy Banjo 16oz
Description: Summer is the time for flavorful session beers and IPA. So why not both? Twangy Banjo is an all-day drinker at just under 5% ABV, but still bursting with passionfruit and papaya aroma from big additions of Vic Secret and Mosaic. The light and crisp character is enhanced by a refreshing lime flavor in the background, but a healthy proportion of wheat in the grain bill provides enough body to let you know you're still drinking an IPA. Easy bitterness from the moderate 49 IBUs just lingers into the finish. This beer is drinkable for days.

Name: Worthy Kama Citrus 12oz
Description: Stir your senses with this perfect blend of Centennial, Simcoe and Equinox hops, kissed with real Mandarin Orange and Grapefruit.

Name: HUB Morning Vibes
Description: Imperial Latte Stout inspired by our favorite morning rituals. Brewed with organic malts, organic hops, organic Nossa Familia Coffee, cocoa, and lactose. Expect big chocolate malt character, deep coffee notes, and cream and dark, boozy textures.

Name: Gigantic Rainbow Supreme 500ml
Description: Rainbow of juicy and tropically delicious hop flavors in this soft and fluffy IPA. Bursting with Citra, Southern Passion, and African Queen hops.

Name: Monkless Brother’s Bier 19oz
Description: If you know Monkless, you know we’re not known for brewing small beers - that said, we wanted a clean sessionable beer to share as the warm summer months approached us. We were inspired by the Trappist tradition of the Belgian Single. Brother’s Bier is a SMaSH beer brewed from Pilsen malt and Sterling hops, and fermented to a nice dry finish with our traditional Trappist yeast strain. A late hop addition of Sterling adds a bit of spicy, citrusy hop aroma and flavor to the quintessential fruity-spicy yeast character of a classic Belgian Single.

Name: Highland Park Hello LA 16oz
Description: This is a bright, pungent IPA that has punchy hops yet still retains good drinkability. Hello, LA finishes dry with not too much body or malt to get in the way of the hops. Lots of new world flavors with the American hop varieties Citra and Mosaic.

Name: Highland Park Timbo 16oz
Description: We took inspiration from both German Pilsners and West Coast IPAs for Timbo Pils. We used more German influenced hops in the kettle which gives the beer a softer bitterness and a nice floral and earthy hop base. We then used Mosaic and Citra for dry hopping to bring out the tropical west coast flavors of mango, riesling grapes, and passionfruit.

Name: Smog City Hoppy Pilsner
Description: West Coast Lager Wai-iti, Idaho 7 & Mandarina Bavaria

Name: Block 15 Intergalactic 16oz
Description: Intergalactic Hop Shop is a luscious, hazy exploration of tropical and citrus hop character. Featuring kettle hop additions of Apollo, Chinook, Azacca and Galaxy hops—with a double dry-hopping of Chinook, Azacca and Galaxy—this cosmically hoppy ale explodes with flavors of passionfruit, tangerine, and pineapple. Enjoy a unique balance of vivid, fruity hop character and approachable drinkability.

Name: Garden Path The Subtle Blend Montmorency Barrels 750ml
Sion Kolsch 11oz
Description: http://www.sion.de Braukunst ist die Kunst, mit den wenigen Zutaten, die das Reinheitsgebot und die Kölschkonvention vorgeben, etwas Besonderes zu schaffen. Reines Wasser aus eigenem Brunnen, obergärige Hefe aus eigener Reinzucht, bestes Gersten- und Weizenmalz und ausgesuchte Hopfensorten – das Ergebnis daraus kann sich schmecken lassen: spritzig-frisch auf der Zunge, feinherb-hopfig am Gaumen, schlank-elegant im Abgang. Einfach guter Geschmack, der folgende Formen annehmen kann.

Name: Hair Of The Dog Matt 12oz
Brewery: Hair of the Dog Brewing Company
Description: Matt was inspired by Matt VandenBerghe and Matt Bonney (Bottleworks and Brouwers in Seattle), who personify the spirit and dedication that has helped craft beer become the vibrant industry it is today. This Beer was originally Brewed to celebrate the tenth anniversary of Bottleworks, and will be released every few years from the Brewery. Matt is made with two Munich malts, two Smoked malts and two types of Belgian candy sugar. It is aged in Kentucky Bourbon and Apple Eau de Vie barrels from Clear Creek distilling. Matt is deep and lush with notes of apple, chocolate and smoke.

Name: Temescal Top Shelf 16oz
Description: <U+2063>This was the first beer we brewed during shelter-in-place and so we went for the good stuff. It’s dry, crisp, has a pleasant lingering snappiness on the palate, and bursting with the ripe flavors and aromas that make Mosaic and Nelson so sought after. We used New Zealand grown Cascade in the whirlpool and dry hop. It’s more fruity and less floral than its American counterpart, and still pleasantly citrusy. Dank tropical and ripe fruit flavors from the Mosaic and Nelson build on the citrusy base.

Name: Fortside Orange Whip 12oz
Description: “Who wants an Orange Whip? Orange Whip? Orange Whip? Three Orange Whips!” No fruit was harmed in the making of this “Juicy” IPA. In fact, there is no “juice” in this IPA. Rather, it is a real IPA that benefits from heaps of El Dorado and Mosaic Hops which give it succulent aromas and flavors of orange, tangerine and grapefruit. We think this IPA predicates Juiciness! Uh, and if you don’t know, now you know.

Name: Tilquin Mure Rullquin 750ml
Description: Stout Rullquin in wich were fermented frozen blackberries at a rate of 260 gr per liter.

Name: Urban Roots All Together 16oz
Description: Our version of All Together, a West Coast IPA. This beer release is part of a worldwide collaboration led by @OtherHalfNYC which will support hospitality professionals across the industry in this time of need.

Name: Sierra Nevada 1980 Pale Ale
Description: Our most popular beer, Sierra Nevada Pale Ale is a delightful interpretation of a classic style. It has a deep amber color and an exceptionally full-bodied, complex character. Generous quantities of premium Cascade hops give the Pale Ale its fragrant bouquet and spicy flavor.

Name: Henhouse Juiced 16oz
Description: So much raspberry puree from Oregon Fruit Products up in this batch of our juiced accompanied by the most sensational sea salt addition! Bright notes of raspberry jam, sour straws, and slight salinity making this here beer oh so delightful!

Name: Fremont Lush 12oz
Description: We bring this tropical treat to you as a reminder of Spring’s coming, its rebirth and promise of sunny days forever. Lush is made with a hand-selected blend of malts and lush, tropical hops to help you bridge the last days of Winter and the coming of the Spring fever. We hope you enjoy this tropical treat, keep your sunglasses handy, and wash away your cares in the coming Spring rains.

Name: Henhouse Kubricks Landing 16oz
Description: As we all know, after filming 2001: A Space Odyssey, director Stanley Kubrick was approached by agents of the Johnson Administration and NASA and was coerced into using the sets and crew of 2001 to creat the footage we are all supposed to blindly believe was Apollo 11 moon landing. I'm not saying we never went to the moon, that's craziness. We just obviously never went on Apollo 11, that footage was just to make it seem we had beat the Soviets there. Riddled with guilt for this massive deception, Kubrick layered The Shining with hidden confessions for his actions and this cinematic apology is still easily his best film. Kubrick's Landing is made with Mosaic, Motueka, and Mandarina Bavaria hops.

Name: Stormbreaker Right As Rain
Description: We set out to make our Pale a Pale, and not a baby IPA. Dry Hopped with Galaxy hops, it’s crisp and easy drinking with mild herbal, floral, citrus, and tropical notes. First wort hopped with US Goldings, Centennial, and Summer, which lends a smoother, less harsh bitterness for a clean finish that is indeed Right as Rain.

Name: Deschutes 2014 Mirror Mirror
Description: 50% aged for 10 months in barrels that once held Oregon Pinot Noir, Tempranillo, and Malbec. Brewed with English malts and Cascade & Millennium hops.

Name: Deschutes Cultivateur 22oz
Description: Provisional saison aged in pinot casks with brettanomyces - crafted at Deschutes Brewery's Public Houses.

Name: Alesong Touch Of Brett - Mandarina 500ml
Description: This dry French-style saison was primary fermented with a blend of Brettanomyces yeasts, lending tropical fruit and spicy aromas. After aging, it was dry-hopped liberally with Mandarina Bavaria hops to complement the ripe pineapple, mango, grapefruit, and rose-like flavors that evolved during the aging time.

Name: Upland Oak & Rose 500ml
Description: Stoaked is a luscious belgian style quadruple that pours a deep amber hue with shades of copper and ruby. Alluring aromas of ripe fig, cherry and subtle spice and caramel pull you in. Maturing for months on oak, Stoaked reveals a profound vanilla character and malty sweetness, supported by a creamy mouthfeel. With a clean finish and a lingering sweetness, this beer is dangerously drinkable for a beverage of its strength.

Name: Lindemans Cuvée Rene 375ml
Description: Gueuze Cuvée René is one of the jewels of our brewery. With its golden colour, its sparkle and its beautiful sherry aromas, this is the queen of gueuzes.

Name: Nightmare Parilla 16oz
Description: Parrilla derives it’s namesake from the way the victim was placed on a metal frame like meat on a BBQ.

Name: Pilsner Urquell 16oz
Description: In 1842, at our brewery in Plzen, brewer Josef Groll introduced the world to the first golden ‘pilsner’ lager, and changed beer forever. His invention soon became the most popular style of beer on the planet.

Name: Ferment Sencha Kombucha
Description: NA

Name: Machine House Ipa
Description: Juice Machine was originally devised and brewed to support our very first trip to Extreme Beer Festival in 2014. It is essentially a marriage of the King Julius malt bill with a hopping schedule more intense than than Very Green. The use of Magnum, Columbus, Amarillo, Citra, and Galaxy creates perhaps our most complex beer with unapologetic flavors of mango, creamy orange sorbet, papaya, and passion fruit with wave after wave of juicy hop flavor. In spite of its intensity, it is pillowy soft and drinks like a true pleasure - the embodiment of the Tree House ideal of hoppy beer. Never abrasive or harsh, It is just as enjoyable on the last sip as it is on the first. It is a mess of hop flavor that takes us to a place that few other of our beers do. It’s hop nirvana

Name: Delirium Red 500ml
Description: Colour and sight: Deep dark red colour, with a light pink, compact and lacing head.

Name: PFriem Ipa
Description: When the first pale ales were sailed around the cape to arrive in India in the early 18th center, outcries of "Zounds!", "Jolly good!", and "Huzzah!" were heard across the East Indian subcontinent. Similar exclamations are to be expected when sniffing the piney aroma and tasting the big hops, huge citrus, and candy-like malt of Pfriem's own IPA. Drink up, guv'nor.

Name: Woodland Empire Peach Party 12oz
Description: Peach and Apricot sour

Name: Achel Bruin
Brewery: Brouwerij der Sint-Benedictusabdij De Achelse Kluis
Description: Achel's regular dubbel, which is available in 33 cl bottles.

Name: Iron Horse Aloha Death
Description: Coconut dark smooth ale

Name: Pelican Lager Cerveza 12oz
Description: Inspired by the lagers of Latin America, this brew is the ultimate easy drinking beer—incredibly refreshing but without sacrificing flavor. The clean six-row malt profile is highlighted by a floral Tettnang hop aroma and supported by a spicy hop finish.

Name: Foam Brewers Things I Imagined
Description: India Pale Ale brewed with lactose and conditioned with pineapple and vanilla bean. Keep cold. Drink Fresh. Time Kills Art.

Name: Foam Brewers Caribou
Description: tasting notes: papaya, dank, clementine, mango

Name: Wild Minds Ultra Wires
Description: West Coast IPA hopped with Cascade, Amarillo and Centennial.

Name: Ex Novo Sex Latin Six/Reveres Ride/The Blue Ox 500ml
Description: Anniversary Series VI. Wild ale 100% spontaneously fermented on whole cluster Gruner grapes and oak aged for 8 months in Chardonnay barrels.

Name: Single Hill Eastside 16oz
Description: Eastern Washington IPA. Showcasing all we know about making amazing IPA we hope this beer does our region proud. Brewed with Yakiman and Treasure valley hops, Idaho pilsner and Palouse munich malt. Layered tropical fruit & citrus flavors.

Name: Crux Farmhouse 500ml
Description: Farmhouse ales originated in the French region of Belgium and offered refreshing relief to seasonal farm workers (“saisonniers”) from the summer heat. When we set out to brew our saison, we were intent on paying homage to its heritage while also giving it our own unique twist. Fermentation coaxes out peppery, herbal and slightly tart attributes, and releases slightly smokey, earthy esters, while a touch of acidulated malt and wheat lends the perfect complement. Resulting in a refreshing palate pleaser regardless of the season.

Name: Portland Cider Peach Berry
Description: Bold, juicy Oregon peaches play with a blend of tart Northwest grown berries for a cider full of sunshine to drink on those grey Portland days. Lively raspberries, blackberries & blueberries burst onto your tongue, just like plucking the fruit from your own backyard. This balanced cider, with a bold peach flavor and slight tartness, pairs well with classics like fish tacos, spicy sausages and corn on the cob.

Name: Montavilla Flam Tap Ipa
Description: Our flagship northwest IPA brewed with Pilsner, Pale, Vienna and Caramel malts and Silverton-grown Centennial hops in the kettle. Dry hopped with citrusy & tropical Falconer’s Flight hops. Listed among Willamette Week’s Top 10 Portland-brewed IPA’s!

Name: Montavilla Helles
Description: This light German-style lager is a respectful nod to the classic German Helles style. An excellent thirst quencher that leans slightly away from the hops and allows the delicious Pilsner malt to shine. 100% German Pilsner malt, German Magnum hops, and German lager yeast.

Name: Montavilla Lil More Righteous
Description: Local’s favorite! A light ale with honey-like flavors coupled with piney Simcoe hops. Dry hopped with Strata hops that exhibit dank-herb, passion fruit, berry, mango and orange aromas. Righteous, indeed!

Name: Montavilla East Glisan
Description: This IPA is loaded with classic "C" hops and dry hopped with Mosaic hops for a mango/pine/stone fruit/dank herbal aroma. Dedicated to our friends at East Glisan Pizza Lounge and named among Willamette Week's Ten Best IPA's in Portland!

Name: Montavilla Bens Barleywine
Description: Brewed in commemoration of Portland brewer and friend, Ben Flerchinger. 50/50 blend of Eastside Distilling Bourbon barrel-aged barleywine (aged for 10 months) and fresh barleywine. British and American malts, American hops and British/American yeasts.

Name: Matchless New Fruit 16oz
Description: This West Coast Style IPA doesn’t shy away from the traditional bitterness of a true IPA while at the same time showcasing bold tropical fruit character. The beer starts off with a nose of ripe tropical fruit, including Pineapple and Papaya. Mango and nectarine follow through on the palate along with notes of cantaloupe and honeydew rounding it out. Nothing is held back with the bright, medium body that allows the showcase of fruit character to shine through. No fruit was harmed during the making of this beer because Hops the New Fruit!

Name: Woodland Empire Old Boise Lager
Description: Made for Treefort! Pacific NW Pilsner malt, flakes maize, NW Mt Hood hops

Name: Incline Seasonal 12oz
Description: Generously dry hopped with a blend of five American varieties. Balanced & approachable. Nose is zesty – like a citrus grove. Notes of mango, tangelo, and watermelon give way to an enjoyably piney bite on the backend. A classic West Coast style IPA.

Name: Adroit Theory White Noise 16oz
Description: A new iteration of our hybrid style IPA. A mixture of hazy and classic American style IPA. Dry Hopped with Mosaic + El Dorado.

Name: Adroit Theory All I See Is Carrion 22oz
Description: Classic Quadruple with Intensely Bold Malt Forward Body. Dark Sugar-like Qualities with Familiar Belgian-style Esters. Creamy Mouthfeel with Rich, Semi-Sweet Finish

Name: Mountains Walking Black Is Beautiful 16oz
Description: Our collaboration with Weathered Souls Brewing brewed with a commitment to donate 100% of the proceeds to The Montana Racial Equity Project. Our version of this Imperial Stout is conditioned on Blackberry, Blueberry and Maple. Huge notes of Maple, Dark Berries and Chocolate overwhelm the pallet while the body provides a mouth coating silkiness that gives way to an exciting Berry Pancake flavor explosion.

Name: Heater Allen Zwickel 16oz
Description: Brewer Lisa created this recipe after a visit to Mahr's Brau in Bamberg Germany. Nice and crisp with a refreshing finish, this is the perfect beer on a hot day!

Name: Tumalo Huckleberry Lemon
Description: You won't have to fend off any bears to get the huckleberries in this cider. Northwest berries come together with a touch of lemon for a refreshing combination of sweet and tart.

Name: 3F Hommage 750ml
Description: 3 Fonteinen Hommage is the result of macerating hand-picked whole sour cherries and raspberries on young lambic for at least four months, in a proportion of 760 to 800 grams of raspberries and 200 to 240 grams of sour cherries per litre of lambic. This fruit lambic is then blended again with more lambic to obtain a minimum intensity of 35% fruit. Hommage is a bodied raspberry lambic beer, with an intense deep red forest fruit bouquet. This unfiltered and unpasteurised lambic is all-natural with no artificial juices, syrups, or sugars added.

Name: Urban Roots Black Is Beautiful 12oz
Description: Black Is Beautiful is an initiative led by San Antonio’s Weathered Souls Brewing that was created to bring awareness to the injustices that many people of color face every day. The mission is to bridge the gap that’s been around for ages and provide a platform to show that the brewing community is an inclusive place for everyone of any color.

Name: Moonraker Citra Double Crush 16oz
Description: Our single-hop double IPA series featuring Citra delivers intense flavors and aroms of melon, guava, lychee, mango and grapefruit. Unfined and unfiltered as usual. This is a double IPA, please crush responsibly.

Name: Silver Moon Maui Wowing 12oz
Description: While we can't all live in Maui, this beer will take your taste buds there. A tropical explosion of flavor followed by a rich and complex hop finish. This beer is a legendary among Silver Moon Brews. Get it while you can!

Name: Ommegang Rosetta 12oz
Description: The time-honored Belgian tradition of aging and blending fruit beers is lovingly expressed in this lively creation, named for legendary brewmaster Rosa Merckx of Liefmans, our sister blendery in Belgium where this beer is crafted.

Name: Fremont Disco Wolf 12oz
Description: Disco Wolf is brewed for the party animal that won’t let the party stop. This fruit forward double IPA is brewed to be dangerously approachable with a moderately bitter bite.

Name: Crux Raspberry Fingers/Battlestar 16oz
Description: Always looking to get our hands dirty, we went wild crafting this fruit-forward ale brewed with raspberries and steeped with citrusy, floral fingers of Buddha’s Hand as well as lemongrass and lemon zest. Slightly tart with an underlying sweetness, this unique ale is balanced by a smooth malt body featuring flaked oats and malted wheat for a sessionable warm weather beer like no other.

Name: Ayinger Altbarisch Dunkel 500ml
Description: Up until the Second World War, dark beer was the predominant beer type in the Munich area. The hard water found in the region played a special role in producing this specialty. In his book “Beer International”, the world-renowned English beer writer, Michael Jackson, accurately describes the Ayinger “Altbairisch Dunkel” as: “A good example of its kind. Impenetrably dark with a golden-brown gleam when held up to the light, and with a warm aroma and malty taste, while summoning up coffee taste sensations on going down. It is brewed from five types of malt (two of which are torrified dark), and it is only lightly hopped.” It is produced using the traditional double fermentation process.

Name: Oakshire Key Lime Kolsch 16oz
Description: Key-Lime-ity Honey Kolsch is our seasonal German-style ale brewed with coffee blossom honey and fermented cold for a smooth crisp taste. We then condition the beer on Key Lime Puree, creating a mesmerizing experience, and helping transport you to the warm months ahead!

Name: Reubens Bloody Crikey/lemon-lime Pilsner22oz
Description: Blood Orange & Amarillo hops

Name: Buoy Decapitator 500ml
Description: Brewed with intention and diligence, our Decapitator Doppelbock harkens back to the traditions of Monastic Germany. Big malt aromatics lead with toasty graham cracker, toffee and fig. Smooth and sneaky, supported by warming alcohol notes and subtle stone fruit esters.

Name: Boss Rambler Maui Babe
Description: DDH West Coast IPA w/ Citra, Simcoe, Amarillo

Name: Boss Rambler Sea doodle
Description: DDH Hazy IPA w/ Citra, Cashmere, El Dorado

Name: Dieu Du Ciel Aphrodite
Description: Black ale with aromas and flavours of vanilla, dark chocolate, bourbon and roasted malt. The vanilla and cocoa marry nicely, without out-competing each other, to produce a surprisingly well balanced beer. This beer is mildly hoppy, but the cocoa introduces a touch of bitterness. Its colour may be intimidating, but it is a very smooth beer within reach of most beer drinkers. This highly appreciated dessert beer is brewed with organic fair-trade cocoa and first rate vanilla beans.

Name: Dansk Orin’s Skul
Description: Nordic Honey Wine with Sour Apple Juice, Hops and Cinnamon Added.

Name: Skookum Eternal Return 16oz
Description: Dopplebock aged in 4th use bourbon barrels.

Name: Skookum Can It 16oz
Description: Hoppy rye/oat pale. An IPA in pales clothing.

Name: Varietal Casita 16oz
Description: Our version of a Mexican style adjunct lager. Brewed with corn for a light, crisp body and entirely brewed with Palisade hops for a bright and fruity finish.

Name: 2 Towns Good Limes Roll 500ml
Description: Fresh & Tangy, let the Good Limes Roll with this easy-drinking cider crafted with fresh-pressed apples, key lime and blue agave.

Name: DeGarde The Lucy 750ml
Description: Lambic inspired with muscat grapes

Name: Chuckanut Single Hop Lager - Trident 500ml
Description: Our sixth rendition of the Single Hop Lager Series uses one the specialized blend Trident made with 3 Pacific NW hop varietals. This special blend creates a hop forward punch of citrus, tropical and passion fruit characteristics and aromas

Name: Brewing Projekt Tart XL Berryzplosion 16oz
Description: Malt beverage with Blueberry, Blackberry, Raspberry, Strawberry, Cherry, Guava and Marshmallow flavor

Name: Brewing Projekt Smoofee (raspberry/Mandarin) 16oz
Beer: Smoofee Sour - Raspberry Mandarin And Vanilla
Description: A Sour fella this time w/Raspberry, Mandarin & a little drip drop of Vanilla. Hot diggity dang get ready to Blend it like Beckham with this smoothie-esque thicc boi. 7.59% ABV. <U+2063>
